**REPORT #3 - Data Security Incident**
**Case ID:** DS-2024-1156
**Subject:** Dr. Priya Kapoor, Research Analyst
**Complainant:** IT Security Team
**Date:** March 22, 2024

**Complaint Summary:**
Automated security system flagged unusual data transfer activity from Dr. Kapoor's workstation to external cloud storage service.

**Evidence Collected:**
- Security logs show 847MB transferred to personal Dropbox account on March 18, 2024
- Transfer occurred at 11:43 PM, outside normal business hours
- Files included research datasets labeled "Project_Aurora_Raw_Data_2024"
- Interview with Dr. Kapoor: She was preparing for conference presentation and needed to work from home due to child care emergency
- Email trail confirms Dr. Kapoor requested remote access approval from supervisor on March 18 at 6:15 PM
- Supervisor approved via email at 7:33 PM with instruction to "use secure method to transfer necessary files"
- Company VPN was experiencing outages that evening (IT ticket #8847 confirms)
- Dr. Kapoor used company-approved Dropbox Business account (not personal account - initial flag was miscategorized)
- All files were deleted from cloud storage on March 20 after presentation was completed

**Conclusion:** INNOCENT - Legitimate business need with supervisor approval, used approved secure platform, followed up appropriately.

